The course deals with the racial and national/ethnic stereotypes and discusses their formation during the history. The course concentrates especially to the period from the 18th century up to the first half of the 20th century. After a general introduction of the theoretical issues and the terminology, the issues of the Otherness and  prejudice are discussed. 
The course consists of lectures, seminars and independent reading.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The main purpose of the course is to give an overview  of the formation of the ethnic  prejudice and stereotypes and its influence to  history.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student has an overview of the historical develpoments  and processes of history, knows thoroughly various theoretical conceptions. Is able to present his/her views in the form of scientific discussion or essay.
